column9: Hello Hi-desert
Hello
Can you do me a favor? Please go to @176, 273
Sure
I would like to borrow one of your trucks for a moment.
OK, where do you want it sent to.
@167,274 would work.
don't build a stop there, just send it to that waypoint!
sorry missed it, let's try again...
It will be back
Thank you!
What just happened?
I used a little bug to take your truck, copied it in the depot so I could have one, and sent it back on its way!
Now you'll just need to remove that waypoint from its schedule!
Ahhh, you wanted an obselete engine unit, right? of was it for kicks?
Oh and the waypoint removed itself
yes, I wanted that obsolete truck. Thanks for putting up with me!
well, i guess its true you learn something new everyday.
It can also be done with trains, though a bit more complex.
How can it be done with trains?
You have to make a public track first and then connect two networks together, then place depot on a public rail stub.
:0, ok i got it now. when anothers player vehicle goes into your own depot, does it retain its player id ?
Yes and no :). It does if I send it back on its way immediately, but if I change its schedule or dissasemble it, no
or it looks like your own, yet when started, it returns to the other player
Bye fifty
